        <p><strong>Jeremy D. Allaire</strong> is an American born technologist and Internet entrepreneur.</p>
        <p>He is currently CEO and founder of the digital currency company Circle and Chairman of the Board of Brightcove.</p>
        <p>With his brother <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Joseph Allaire', 'P'); ?>, he co-founded <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Allaire Corporation', 'C'); ?> in 1995 and created <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('ColdFusion', 'L'); ?>, the first commercial web application server platform.</p>
        <p>Allaire Corp. had a successful IPO in January 1999 and was subsequently acquired by rival <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Macromedia', 'C'); ?> in 2001.</p>
